kdna-remote-server
Copyright 2026 KDNA Authors

This product includes software developed at
https://github.com/aikdna/kdna-remote-server

This server is a structural selection layer for KDNA `.kdna`
assets in `remote` access mode. It transmits only task-scoped
projections, does not transmit or externally store the full
judgment payload, and makes no content-certification claim. See
LICENSE for the full Apache 2.0 license text. See README.md for
the self-hosting invariant and layer-isolation guarantees.

The server does not generate content-certification fields or claims per SPEC
§13.1 and the layer-isolation rules in `docs/REMOTE_MODE.md`. Asset-authored
text is preserved verbatim; vocabulary inside selected judgment content is not
treated as a server claim.

The source repository includes the unmodified npm 11.17.0 third-party
distribution archive as integrity-pinned test and release-tooling input. That
archive is excluded from this package's published artifact. npm's own
`package/LICENSE` is included inside the archive and governs npm and its
bundled components; this repository's Apache 2.0 license does not replace or
override those third-party terms.
